\subsection{Novelty Relative to Prior Work}

Four distinct novelty claims differentiate ApexS from a baseline sprint optimizer,
all grounded in the implemented repository:
\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=*,itemsep=1pt,topsep=2pt]
	\item \textbf{Team-adaptive weight learning}: rather than relying on fixed a priori
	      coefficients, urgency, value, and alignment are inferred from each team's
	      historical completion record.
	\item \textbf{Four-constraint operational feasibility}: capacity limits, risk
	      threshold, skill availability, and dependency satisfaction are all active
	      constraints in the current code path, enforced simultaneously.
	\item \textbf{Bidirectional story-level explainability}: concrete operational causes
	      and confidence scores accompany acceptance and rejection decisions for every
	      story processed.
	\item \textbf{Closed decision-support workflow}: the system spans the full sequence
	      of upload, context learning, optimization, explanation review, plan approval,
	      and Jira-compatible export without requiring external tooling.
\end{enumerate}
The novelty is therefore fundamentally architectural and workflow-centric, not
merely algorithmic.
Table~\ref{tab:related-comparison} (Section~\ref{sec:related}) provides a
comparative positioning against prior work.

\begin{table}[t]
	\caption{Novelty Positioning Against Common Sprint-Planning Tool Patterns}
	\label{tab:novelty-summary}
	\centering\small
	\begin{tabularx}{\columnwidth}{lYY}
		\toprule
		Capability                             & Typical research prototype & ApexS \\
		\midrule
		Historical team adaptation             &
		Often fixed weights or heuristics      &
		Learned urgency/value/alignment weights from team history                   \\
		Hard planning constraints              &
		Usually partial or task-specific       &
		Capacity, risk, skill, and dependency constraints in one code path          \\
		Decision explanation                   &
		Often absent or limited to final score &
		Per-story explanations for selected and rejected items                      \\
		Workflow closure                       &
		Often optimizer only                   &
		Upload, generate, explain, approve, and export                              \\
		\bottomrule
	\end{tabularx}
\end{table}

