\section{Results and Discussion}
\label{sec:results}

\subsection{Dataset Characteristics}

The empirical evaluation is organized around the four final datasets used in the
study.
Spring XD, Usergrid, and Aurora are treated as supporting comparative corpora
because each provides a project-specific perspective on planner behavior under
distinct backlog characteristics.
TAWOS is designated as the primary real-world evaluation dataset because it offers
the largest corpus, explicit sprint groupings, and richer dependency evidence
through issue links.
The discussion therefore proceeds from dataset characterization to planning
performance, followed by baseline comparison, distributional analysis, and a
qualitative case study.

Table~\ref{tab:dataset-summary} serves as the anchor profile for the remainder of
this section; all subsequent performance tables and figures are derived from the
same frozen snapshot to ensure internal consistency.
The recommended narrative sequence introduces the three project-specific corpora
first, then positions TAWOS as the strongest external-validation setting.

