The dataset profile establishes the empirical foundation for subsequent analysis.
Aggregated across the four frozen snapshots, the study encompasses 18,036 stories
and 486 sprint groups.
With 14,738 stories and 343 sprint groups, TAWOS is far and away the largest corpus;
Spring XD, Usergrid, and Aurora contribute 2,360, 512, and 426 stories respectively.
Among the cleaned snapshots, TAWOS is also the sole dataset containing non-empty
dependency rows (673), a distinction that must be stated explicitly when interpreting
dependency-aware planning results.
Mean business value spans 5.09 in Spring XD to 6.03 in TAWOS, while mean risk
ranges from 0.36 to 0.52 across the four corpora.

\subsection{Performance Evaluation}

Planning performance is assessed at two complementary levels.
First, the frozen CSV snapshots establish the scale and structural properties of the
four-dataset evaluation pool.
Second, run-dependent planning metrics are captured from ApexS executions conducted
on Spring XD, Usergrid, Aurora, and TAWOS under controlled conditions.

