Seeded runs on all four datasets produce nontrivial learning behavior rather than
degenerate constant outputs. Across learned-MILP all-constraint runs, mean test
metrics are MAE 0.3027, $R^2$ 0.1512, F1 0.8763, and ROC-AUC 0.7075, indicating that
the weight learner captures usable completion signal while remaining dataset-sensitive.

\paragraph{Repository-Grounded Planning Behavior.}

To assess operational planning behavior in a controlled and repeatable manner,
all four frozen datasets were evaluated at a fixed sprint capacity of 30 story points
and risk threshold $\tau=0.7$.
Aggregate outcomes from these runs appear in
Tables~\ref{tab:performance-metrics} and \ref{tab:baseline-comparison}, while
Table~\ref{tab:planning-scenarios} provides a compact scenario-based interpretability
summary.
In addition to aggregate outcomes, the updated backend emits per-run diagnostic
artifacts: (i) feasibility counts (total stories and counts filtered by risk,
skill, dependency, and status) and (ii) score-distribution summaries
(minimum, maximum, mean) over feasible candidates. These diagnostics were used to
verify that observed plan differences across scenarios arise from explicit
constraint effects rather than silent preprocessing or scaling artifacts.

