Table~\ref{tab:planning-scenarios} shows deterministic ablation behavior under
explicit hard-constraint toggles. Disabling capacity causes the largest shift in all
datasets. Disabling risk, skill, or dependency has limited effect in Spring XD,
Usergrid, and Aurora under the evaluated threshold and skill settings, while TAWOS
shows a measurable risk-value trade-off when risk gating is removed. These outcomes
directly answer \textbf{RQ1}: the optimizer responds to hard constraints in a
traceable and reproducible manner.

