Learned MILP outperforms greedy and random baselines in delivered value on all four
datasets under identical capacity and risk settings. Relative to fixed-weight and
context-only MILP, learned MILP improves value in every dataset but does not
uniformly reduce selected risk, most notably on TAWOS where value gains come with
higher average risk inside the allowed threshold.

